 <li>Perform the budgeting and forecasting role for all Dutch entities, except S.C. Johnson Europlant B.V.</li>
 <li>In conjunction with the European Shared Service Centre maintain financial statements and underlying records, which adequately reflect all transactions in accordance with S.C. Johnson, fiscal and statutory accounting policies/requirements, handling queries and matters raised by external and internal auditors.</li>
 <li>In collaboration with internal audit, monitor control systems which safeguard the company''s assets and financial condition, in line with S.C. Johnson''s policies and procedures. </li>
 <li>Identify improvements in business processes or make recommendations to drive cost savings and tax efficiencies.</li>
 <li>Act as contact person for all Dutch entities on Corporate Insurance matters.</li>
 <li>Local point of contact and coordinator for all regulatory, statutory and tax enquiries. </li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Required competencies: </strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>Accountant/Financial level</li>
 <li>Fluent Dutch and English</li>
 <li>Excellent communication skills and establish trusted relationships with the MITSA, Regional SSC, Corporate Tax, Insurance, and appropriate statutory and tax external companies.</li>
 <li>Demonstrated ability to judge organisational dynamics (who needs to be informed, who had vested interests, which external parties should be involved).</li>
 <li>Desired knowledge of Treasury related processes</li>
 <li>Able to work autonomously and a good team player.</li>
</ul>
<br>Werken met Huxley
