<p><b><u>About us</u></b></p>
<p>In the Netherlands, where 2100 employees are based, we are located in four cities: Huizen, Delft, Eindhoven and Hengelo (HQ). Together with an extensive ecosystem of knowledge partners, customers and suppliers, we work on radars for naval vessels, cyber security solutions, transportation systems, communication equipment for land forces, cryogenic cooling solutions and research &amp; development for radar tech (in collaboration with TU Delft).</p>
<p>The software department of the Application Engineering cluster is responsible for the software development in Combat Management and Radar- and Optical sensors for worldwide navies- and defense systems. The work is performed in multi-disciplinary agile teams with specialists in software/system/test engineering and functional design.</p>
<p><b><u>About the assignment</u></b></p>
<p>Delivering quality is a must in the field of mission management systems. To meet that goal we invest heavily in testing to prove the applications are ready to be delivered to customers around the world that depend on it. You have a chance to aid in this development by providing a working concept of a continuous delivery system.</p>
<p>We want you to investigate continuous delivery techniques in our mission management software to reduce the effort needed to deliver a qualified mission management solution. You will be involved in building a modular software framework that aids in fully automatic testing, together with reporting that suits our quality assurance processes and software. Will you be able to deliver a complex solution to a critical customer with one click?</p>
<p><b><u>Affinity</u></b></p>
<p>Linux, Java, User Interface, Quality, Continuous Integration</p>
<p><b><u>Thales offers… </u></b></p>
<ul>
 <li>An interesting internship or graduation assignment in an international high tech environment</li>
 <li>An open and flexible working environment</li>
 <li>An excellent internship allowance</li>
 <li>Its own student association where you can participate in educational and fun activities. </li>
</ul>
