INSERT INTO public.vacancy VALUES ('7d42c0a4-eec5-4cde-b2cc-6ec125f7d909', '<p><strong>Magento Developer</strong></p>
<p>Are you an IT specialist and do you also believe e-commerce will at a certain point take over physical shopping? If you''re this forward thinking person then I might be looking for you. For a company in the area of Leiden I''m looking for a Medior Magento Developer.</p>
<p><strong>About the company</strong></p>
<p>This company started 25 years ago focussing on marketing and communication. 13 years later they successfully added an IT component and now more than 65 international retail companies, 5.000 (online) stores, 50.000 employees and millions of shoppers are using their products and services.</p>
<p><strong>Their offer</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>Great Salary and benefits that''ll make you happy</li>
 <li>A passionate and inspiring environment</li>
 <li>A fulltime position as Medior Magento Developer</li>
 <li>Continuously challenge yourself</li>
 <li>Working for big clients</li>
 <li>Good travel allowance</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Tasks</strong></p>
<p>Within this company you''ll be joining a development team with 25 colleagues sharing the same passion. They work with scrum teams of 3-4 people and you''ll have a lot of contact with your colleagues and therefore it''s easier to brainstorm about using new techniques, ways to implement things and other job related matters. The company''s culture is best characterised as a place where you can fully develop yourself and use your maximum potential. In your role as Medior Magento Developer you''ll realise and optimize big e-commerce projects and you''ll create innovative solutions for the clients. You have to be passionate about programming and use your creativity to conquer technical challenges.</p>
<p><strong>What they''re looking for</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>Proficient in English, Dutch is a nice to have.</li>
 <li>Your code is easy to read and transfer</li>
 <li>You''re not scared of client contact</li>
 <li>Affinity with design</li>
 <li>Higher Education thinking level</li>
 <li>Experience with PHP/HTML/CSS/JavaScript/MySQL</li>
 <li>Living in the Netherlands, preferably in Leiden area<br> </li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Nice to have</strong></p>
<ul>
 <li>Knowledge of Agile/Scrum</li>
 <li>Ambition to become a fullstack developer</li>
 <li>Experience with Magento</li>
 <li>Experience with XMLRPC, SOAP or REST</li>
 <li>Experience with GIT</li>
 <li>You''ve heard of development patterns like ''factory'', ''singleton'', ''observer'', ''prototype''</li>
