<p>Experience deploying and maintaining data science frameworks;</p>
<p>python;</p>
<p>matlab;</p>
<p>kubernetes;</p>
<p>deep learning frameworks;</p>
<p>containers (docker and/or singularity)</p>
<p>GPU computing;</p>
<p>Experience with executing data science work is a pre;</p>
<br> <b>Personal skills</b>
<p>Highly motivated team player.</p>
<p>Shows initiative and problem solving attitude.</p>
<p>Vision and opinion.</p>
<p>Independent, accurate, systematic approach, problem solving.</p>
<p>Pragmatic, practical, flexible and committed to quality.</p>
<p>Excellent communication skills and proficiency in the English language.</p> Bedrijfsinformatie <b>Context of the position</b>
<p>A sub-department within the IT organization is IT Competence Center Big Data &amp; Advanced Analytics. Their vision is that they want to unleash the power of innovative data analytics &amp; collaboration to make a difference for ASML. They do this by providing high end analytics capabilities and collaboration services to the ASML eco-system"</p>
<p>The Data engineering expert will be part of the Data analytics platform, applications enablement, team (6 fte) which is part of the Competence Center Big Data &amp; Advanced Analytics.</p>
