<p>Niveau: HBO/WO</p>
<p>Studierichting(en): Software Engineering</p>
<p>Titel van de opdracht: Validating visual aspects of combat management systems</p>
<p><b><u>About us</u></b></p>
<p>With 80.000 talents working in 68 countries, we are one of the biggest high-tech employers in the field of safety and security. In the Netherlands, where 2000 employees are based, we are located in four cities: Huizen, Delft, Eindhoven and Hengelo (HQ). Together with an extensive ecosystem of knowledge partners, customers and suppliers, we work on radars for naval vessels, cyber security solutions, transportation systems, communication equipment for land forces, cryogenic cooling solutions, research &amp; development for radar tech (in collaboration with TU Delft).<br><br>The software department of the Application Engineering cluster is responsible for the software development in Combat Management and Radar- and Optical sensors for worldwide navies- and defense systems. The work is performed in multi-disciplinary agile teams with specialists in software/system/test engineering and functional design.</p>
<p><u>About the assignment</u></p>
<p>Delivering quality is a must in the field of combat management systems. To meet that goal we invest heavily in automated testing to prove the applications are ready to be delivered to customers around the world that depend on it. You have a chance to aid in this development by providing a working concept of a visual inspection software component.</p>
<p>We want you to investigate visual inspection techniques in our combat management software to reduce the effort needed to deliver a qualified combat management solution. You will be involved in building a modular software component that aids in automatic visual testing by using image recognition techniques or other applicable technology, together with reporting that suits our quality assurance processes and software. Will you be able to validate complex visual aspects of our combat management software with one press of a button?</p>
