INSERT INTO public.vacancy VALUES ('4ce89e6a-046f-463f-a1cb-b0de929fc4cc', 'In fast changing markets, customers worldwide rely on Thales. Thales is a business where brilliant people from all over the world come together to share ideas and inspire each other. In aerospace, transportation, defence, security and space, our achitects design innovative solutions that make our tomorrow''s possible.
<p>Soort opdracht: Afstudeeropdracht</p>
<p>Niveau: HBO</p>
<p>Studierichting: Informatica/Computer Science</p>
<p>Titel van de opdracht:</p>
<p><b>Distributed Building environment met source dependencies</b></p>
<p><b><u>About us</u></b></p>
<p>With 80.000 talents working in 68 countries, we are one of the biggest high-tech employers in the field of safety and security. In the Netherlands, where 2000 employees are based, we are located in four cities: Huizen, Delft, Eindhoven and Hengelo (HQ). Together with an extensive ecosystem of knowledge partners, customers and suppliers, we work on radars for naval vessels, cyber security solutions, transportation systems, communication equipment for land forces, cryogenic cooling solutions, research &amp; development for radar tech (in collaboration with TU Delft).</p>
<p><u>About the assignment</u></p>
<p>Within the Sensor department we use Maven as primary build tool; even for our C and</p>
<p>C++ projects.</p>
<p>Maven as build tool works fine for language which have platform independent</p>
<p>deliverables (e.g. Java jars), but loses efficiency when deliverables are sources or</p>
<p>platform dependent binaries.</p>
<p>For this assignment the student needs to research and create a proof on concept solution</p>
<p>for an alternative for our Maven C / C++ projects.</p>
<p>The solution should:</p>
<ul>
 <li>Support building for multiple target platforms</li>
 <li>Support code generation phases</li>
 <li>Support for dependency management: - For source dependencies with remote caching (preferred) - Or binary dependencies for multiple platform</li>
 <li>Support the CLion IDE and optionally the Eclipse IDE</li>
 <li>Improves the performance and efficiency compared to our current Maven based C/C++ projects</li>
</ul>
<p>Optionally the solution should also:</p>
<ul>
 <li>Support building Docker or Open Container Initiative (OCI ) complaint container images</li>
 <li>Support building debug symbols in separate files and</li>
 <li>Support debugging with use of a symbol database using build ids.</li>
</ul>
<p>This solution should include the ability to build for different target platforms, be able</p>
<p><u>Affinity</u></p>
<p>Build tooling</p>
<p>Technologies involved: C++, CMake, Maven, Bazel, Buck, Pants, Ant, Ivy</p>
<p><b><u>Thales offers… </u></b></p>
<ul>
 <li>An interesting internship or graduation assignment in an international high tech environment</li>
 <li>An open and flexible working environment</li>
 <li>An excellent internship allowance</li>
 <li>Its own student association where you can participate in educational and fun activities. </li>
</ul>
<p><b><u>Interested?</u></b></p>
<p>Direct solliciteren? Gebruik dan je eigen, persoonlijke profiel om jouw interesse aan ons kenbaar te maken en kies voor ‘Apply now’.</p>
<p>Would you like to apply directly? Then click on the button ‘Apply now’ to show your interest.<br>Please keep in mind that we can only consider students who are enrolled at a school during the whole internship period for our internships and graduation assignments.</p>
<p>At Thales we provide CAREERS and not only jobs. With Thales employing 80,000 employees in 68 countries our mobility policy enables thousands of employees each year to develop their careers at home and abroad, in their existing areas of expertise or by branching out into new fields. Together we believe that embracing flexibility is a smarter way of working. Great journeys start here, apply now!</p>   <strong>Type vacature:</strong>  Intern   Vaardigheden
